---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../../components/Prose.astro';
import { whatsappLink } from '../../config';

const contactMessage = 'Hi Vooth, I have a question about personal data (Privacy Policy).';
const contactHref = whatsappLink(contactMessage);
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Vooth collects, uses, stores, and deletes your personal data, under Indonesian Law No. 27 of 2022 (PDP Law)."
>
  <Prose
    title="Vooth Privacy Policy"
    updated="Version 1.0 (draft) · Legal basis: Law No. 27 of 2022 (PDP Law)"
  >
    <p>
      This page explains how <strong>Vooth</strong> ("we") collects, uses, stores, and deletes your personal
      data. It follows Indonesian Law No. 27 of 2022 on Personal Data Protection (the PDP Law). The Indonesian
      version at <a href="/privasi">/privasi</a> is the authoritative text.
    </p>

    <div
      class="not-prose rounded-xl border border-highlight/30 bg-highlight-soft p-4 text-sm text-ink"
    >
      <strong>Draft status.</strong> The Vooth data-controller legal entity is still being finalized.
      In the meantime, personal-data questions are handled directly via Vooth WhatsApp, with Endy Muhardin
      as the responsible person. The legal entity name, mailing address, and official email will appear
      here before this policy takes full effect.
    </div>

    <h2>1. Data Controller Identity</h2>
    <p>The controller of personal data for the Vooth service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Responsible person:</strong> Endy Muhardin</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact:</strong>
        <a href={contactHref} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vooth WhatsApp</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Questions, complaints, or requests about your personal data can be sent via the contact above.
      We respond within 14 business days at most.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
    <h3>2.1 Your Photos</h3>
    <p>
      Photos you produce using Vooth, including the composite with the frame and moment context you
      chose.
    </p>
    <h3>2.2 Transaction Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Session ID (random, internal)</li>
      <li>Chosen package and payment amount</li>
      <li>Payment method and payment status</li>
      <li>Photo creation and access timestamps</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>2.3 Technical Data</h3>
    <p>When you access your photo download link:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your device IP address</li>
      <li>Browser and operating system (user agent)</li>
      <li>Access timestamp</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>2.4 Consent Records</h3>
    <p>
      When you give consent, we record the timestamp, the policy version in effect, and the agreed
      retention period.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not collect:</strong> name, phone number, personal email, ID number, biometric data,
      GPS location, or any data beyond what is listed above.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Processing Purposes</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Delivering the service you paid for:</strong> storing your photo so you can download it
        via a unique link.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Processing payment</strong> for your session.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Supporting event operations:</strong> aggregate summaries (transaction count, revenue
        per event) in the operator dashboard.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Meeting legal obligations</strong> where there is an official request from an authorized
        body.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not use your data for:</strong> advertising, AI model training, facial recognition,
      profiling, sale to third parties, or behavioral analytics.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
    <p>
      Processing is based on the <strong>explicit consent</strong> you give before the session begins
      (Article 20(2)(a) of the PDP Law). Without this consent the service cannot be provided, because
      we would be unable to deliver your photo.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Retention and Automatic Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Your photos are stored for <strong>30 days</strong> after the transaction completes (configurable
      by the operator within 7–90 days). After that period, your photos are deleted automatically by a
      scheduled daily process. Transaction records (without photos) are kept for 5 years as accounting
      evidence.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights as a Data Subject</h2>
    <p>Under Articles 5–11 of the PDP Law, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Access</strong> your personal data — the photo download link is that access mechanism.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Delete</strong> your photo at any time before the retention period ends.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — deleting the photo is equivalent to withdrawing consent.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Correct</strong> data if there is an error.</li>
      <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing.</li>
      <li><strong>File a complaint</strong> with the Personal Data Protection Authority.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Data is stored on servers located in Indonesia.</li>
      <li>
        Server access is restricted to authorized operators via SSH key authentication and basic
        auth for the dashboard.
      </li>
      <li>
        Communication between your device and our server is protected with TLS encryption (HTTPS).
      </li>
      <li>Photo download links use a cryptographic signature (HMAC) with limited validity.</li>
      <li>
        Your photos are not stored on foreign cloud services, not uploaded to social media, and not
        shared with third parties.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Sharing Data with Third Parties</h2>
    <p>
      We only share data with third parties where a payment gateway is required to process a
      transaction, or upon an official <strong>legal request</strong> from law enforcement. We do
      <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or trade your data.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
    <p>
      Our photo download pages use no third-party cookies, load no analytics scripts, and use no
      tracking pixels. Only minimal session cookies are used where required for basic security.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Minors</h2>
    <p>
      Vooth is not designed specifically for children under 18. If a customer is a minor, consent
      must be given by a lawful parent or guardian, per Article 25 of the PDP Law.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Policy Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy. Any material change is marked with a new version and
      updated effective date at the top of this page. Consent you have already given remains valid
      for the version in effect when it was given.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Jurisdiction and Dispute Resolution</h2>
    <p>
      This policy is governed by the laws of the Republic of Indonesia. Any dispute is first
      resolved through deliberation; failing that, through the mechanisms set out in the PDP Law and
      its implementing regulations, including submission to the Personal Data Protection Authority
      or a competent judicial forum.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For questions, complaints, or requests about your personal data, reach us on
      <a href={contactHref} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vooth WhatsApp</a>. We respond
      within 14 business days at most.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</MarketingLayout>
